  "title": "URN",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "A unique and semantic identifier using the format:\n\n  œÜrn:<reverse-domain>:<type>[:<subtype1>:<subtype2>:...]:<id>\n\nThis URN-like structure is:\n- based on reversed domain naming (e.g., `org.17711`, `com.example.app`),\n- composable with a variable number of subcategories (type/subtype...),\n- supports either a readable ID (`slug`, `username`, etc.) or a base58-encoded content-based hash (min 10 chars).\n\nInspired by URN, DID, IPFS-style CIDs, and decentralized naming systems.",
  "type": "string",
  "pattern": "^œÜrn:([a-z0-9.-]+(?:\\.[a-z0-9.-]+)*):([a-z0-9._-]+(?::[a-z0-9._-]+)*):([1-9A-HJ-NP-Za-km-z]{10,}|[a-zA-Z0-9_.@-]+)$",
